        .span8
          .article-content
            h4 Get ready for Grok 2014
            p This year is going to be special for Grok. In addition to the amazing 10/20 conversations that we're known for, attendees will get to drive BMWs on a racetrack and hear inspiring talks from keynote speakers. Here are links to where and what's happening this year:
            ul
              li <a href="#location">Location</a>
              li <a href="#schedule">Schedule</a>
              li <a href="#speakers">Speakers</a>
              li <a href="#travel">Getting to Greenville</a>
            p Need to get in touch? <a href="http://twitter.com/greenvillegrok">@GreenvilleGrok</a> / <a href="mailto:grok@theironyard.com">grok@theironyard.com</a>
            hr
            p Excited? We are too. We'll see you in a few weeks. Until then, watch our video from last year and count the days.
            .video-container
              iframe src="http://player.vimeo.com/video/69313375" width="630" height="354" frameborder="0" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen
            h4 <a name="location"></a>Location
            p This year we're gathering at Certus Loft, a gorgeous loft in the historic Huguenot Mill. Here is the address:
            p <blockquote>Huguenot Mill/Nuckasee<br>W Broad St<br>Greenville, SC 29601<br><em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Huguenot+Mill%2FNuckasee/@34.848003,-82.4021485,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x885831ccfd954531:0x93b73edd24f520fe">Directions here</a></em></blockquote>
            hr
            h4 <a name="schedule"></a>Schedule
            p <strong>Wednesday, April 2nd</strong>
            ul
              li 6-10pm - Registration, beer and pretzels
            p <strong>Thursday, April 3rd</strong>
            ul
              li 9:30am - Coffee
              li 10:00am - Welcome
              li 10:15am - Keynote
              li 11:00am - 10/20s
              li 12:30pm - Lunch
              li 1:30pm - Hunger Crunch Demo with Bryan Martin
              li 2:00pm - 10/20s
              li 4:00pm - Code Education and Academy Demos
            p <strong>Friday, April 4th</strong>
            ul
              li 8:00am - BMW Driving (Group 1)
              li 10:00am - 10/20s (Group 2)
              li 11:45am - Lunch (Group 2)
              li 12:30pm - BMW Driving (Group 2)
              li 12:30pm - Lunch (Group 1)
              li 1:30pm - 10/20s (Group 1)
              li 3:30pm - Coffee Break (Group 1)
              li 5:00pm - Keynote
              li 7:00pm - Afterparty!
            p <strong>Saturday, April 5th</strong>
            ul
              li 10:00am - Coffee
              li 10:30am - Special activities
            hr
            h4 <a name="speakers"></a>Speakers
            p <strong>Sam Fogarino</strong> - <em>Interpol</em>
            p Sam is the drummer for Interpol and has worked on several other widely respected projects. He will be talking about ego and the process of creativity. 
            p <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sam_Fogarino">Learn more</a>
            p <strong>Kristian Andersen</strong> - <em>KA+A</em>
            p Founder of an award-winning design firm, successful entrepreneur, angel and VC investor, and father of 5 kids, Kristian is going to talk about the meaning of success. 
            p <a href="http://www.kristian.vc/">Learn more</a>
            hr
            h4 <a name="travel"></a>Getting to Greenville
            p Hop in a car and <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Greenville,+SC/@34.8331685,-82.3628304,13z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x88578f6662fa1105:0xd8aa9d77bf257696">head our way</a> or fly into our beautiful <a href="http://www.gspairport.com/">international airport</a>.



